description.value:
At Calvary, we are committed to holistic, resident focused care. We have created a home environment, which supports your independence. By taking the time to get to know you and understand your medical concerns, we can meet your physical, social, emotional and spiritual needs. Our highly trained and attentive team ensure all residents are cared for with integrity and respect. 
Calvary Muswellbrook Retirement Community offers permanent and respite accommodation to 65 residents in single or companion rooms each with a private ensuite, air-conditioning with temperature control, plus flat screen televisions.
Cafe, Gym, Wellness Centre, Community Gardens, BBQ areas, Children's Play ground
All meals prepared and cooked onsite, hairdressing salon, Sitting rooms with tea and coffee facilities, Entertainment by local groups and schools, bus trips and social outings, Internet access, Religious services provided and Palliative care

subtypes.roomDescription: Premium Single room with ensuite with garden views, large spacious room with private ensuite, plenty of cupboard space, flatscreen wall mounted tv,
subtypes.commonAreaDescription: Enjoy this brand new purpose built facility with secure gardens, cafe, activities room, community garden, children's playground, community bbq areas, gym, wellness centre, hair salon
subtypes.paymentOptions: Residents can choose to pay for their accommodation by a refundable deposit, a daily payment or a combination of both. A refundable deposit is paid as a lump sum amount. A daily payment accrues daily and is paid periodically, for example monthly. A combination payment includes both a partial lump sum and daily payments.

subtypes.roomDescription: Brand new light filled rooms, dual entry doors, large flatbed tv, specially designed beds, garden views, private ensuite. For further details please visit www.calvarycare.org.au
subtypes.additionalAmenities: Postal service, hairdressing and beautician services, allied health, pharmacy supplies
subtypes.additionalCare: Shopping trips, trivia nights, bingo/housie, arts and crafts, word/floor/table games, reminiscence, exercises, movies and music, tours/outings, facility has own bus
subtypes.commonAreaDescription: Secure gardens, activities room, community gardens, children's playground, cafe, gym, wellness centre, hair salon, brand new facility, purpose built. For further details please visit www.calvarycare.org.au

requirementDescription.value:
Each consumer is supported to exercise choice and independence:
i) make decisions about their own care and the way care and services are delivered.
ii) make decisions about when family, friends, carers or others should be involved in their care.
iii) communicate their decisions.
iv) make connections with others and maintain relationships of choice, including intimate relationships.
